SELF WHAT TO DO HAD YOU FACING SO MUCH FORTUNE. ASKING THE PROJECT TEAM POL=
ITELY SO THAT THEY CAN FIX IT? ANYONE COULD BE THE TRAITOR GIVEN ONE BILLIO=
N! I CAN TRUST NOBODY! THE ONLY SOLUTION I CAN COME UP WITH IS SAYING IT IN=
 A _TRUSTED_ ACCOUNT WHILE KEEPING MYSELF _ANONYMOUS_ AND _SAFE_.</p></bloc=
kquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously you do not have to believe th=
is. I just want to point out that it=E2=80=99s =E2=80=A6=C2=A0right? Like l=
et=E2=80=99s say you noticed a bug in a popular crypto network that allows =
anyone to transfer all the money in the network to themselves. What would y=
ou do? How would you assume that bug got there?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">If you noticed a bug like that in the software of a bank, or the Feder=
al Reserve, or Facebook, or whatever, one thing you could do is call up the=
 company=E2=80=99s main number and say =E2=80=9CI have found a bug.=E2=80=
=9D Of course they might ignore you or not understand or not do anything; b=
ig institutions are not always nimble and clever. But if you managed to get=
 on the phone with=C2=A0Jamie Dimon and tell him =E2=80=9Chey there=E2=80=
=99s a bug in your software that lets anyone steal a trillion dollars of de=
posits,=E2=80=9D you would not expect him to respond =E2=80=9Coh sweet=E2=
=80=9D and=C2=A0<em>steal the money himself</em>.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">Whereas with a crypto project, if you managed to get on the =E2=80=
=A6=C2=A0Discord chat? ... with the =E2=80=A6=C2=A0the stateless pseudonymo=
us developer? ... who seems to =E2=80=A6=C2=A0write most of its Medium post=
s?=C2=A0=E2=80=A6 and you said =E2=80=9Chey there=E2=80=99s a bug in your s=
oftware that lets anyone steal a billion dollars of user money,=E2=80=9D an=
d he responded =E2=80=9Coh sweet I=E2=80=99m gonna steal it,=E2=80=9D or fo=
r that matter =E2=80=9Cyes I put it there so that I could steal it and now =
I will,=E2=80=9D you would not be=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>surprised. I don=
=E2=80=99t mean to cast any aspersions on Poly Network or anything; I just =
mean, as a general matter, a whole lot of crypto projects really are design=
ed to steal all their users=E2=80=99 money.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">So if you found a bug like this, a thought process like =E2=80=9CI a=
m going to steal all the money myself so that no one else steals it, and th=
en give it back once the bug is fixed, and maybe keep a few million dollars=
=C2=A0for my trouble=E2=80=9D would not be totally unreasonable. I want to =
be clear that I am=C2=A0<em>very=C2=A0</em>skeptical that this was actually=
 this hacker=E2=80=99s thought process. I just mean it=E2=80=99s a plausibl=
e funny thought process.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=
